The paper deals with rate-distortion problems and source coding, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of side information and the Markov form also suggest the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the analysis of trade-offs and the exploration of different message rates suggest the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
